+
+### UC-7 — TriCNES deferred-DISABLE ported + REFUTED (`mc-r1-dmc-defer-disable`)
+The wf-dma-port mandate (faithful coupled bus+DMA+DMC port) re-examined the ONE `$4015` mechanism the
+committed step-1 (`mc-r1-dmc-defer-4015`) explicitly SKIPPED: the deferred **disable**. Step-1 kept the
+disable's `bytes_remaining = 0` IMMEDIATE; TriCNES (Emulator.cs 1219-1223) defers it to the put?5:6
+`APU_DelayedDMC4015` expiry while the gating status `APU_Status_DelayedDMC` clears at once (bit-4 read =
+`bytes != 0 && status`, 9260). Hypothesis (mechanically plausible): the implicit-abort sweep's
+`STA $4015`(disable)→re-enable loop re-arms a fresh load DMA at EVERY offset because the immediate
+disable makes the re-enable see `bytes_remaining == 0` (passing `StartDMCSample`'s `if BytesRemaining==0`
+gate); deferring the clear makes the re-enable see `bytes_remaining > 0` → no re-load → `$4000` reads 00.
+
+Ported faithfully behind `mc-r1-dmc-defer-disable` (default-off; new fields `deferred_disable_pending` +
+`dmc_status_delayed`; defer the clear in `apply_dmc_4015`, mature it at the `delayed_4015_delay` expiry,
+gate bit-4 on the status). **Floor (flag-off) byte-identical; nes-cpu unit canary 33/33.**
+
+**RESULT — REFUTED.** Measured on R1 floor + `mc-r1-dmc-defer-4015`:
+- Implicit `$500` sweep: `01x16` (UNCHANGED — still over-fires at every offset, vs Key1 `00x10 01 01 00x4`).
+- Explicit `$520` sweep: `00x16` (UNCHANGED, vs Key2 `00x10 01 00x5`).
+- AccuracyCoin: **9 → 10 fails** — it REGRESSES `DMA + $2002 Read` (was passing on the floor), because
+  holding `bytes_remaining` alive 5-6 extra cycles perturbs the DMA-drives-bus interaction with the
+  `$2002` read (the same simultaneous-constraint wall as the internal-bus save/restore: anything that
+  changes how long the DMC drives/holds the bus breaks a passing DMA+register test).
+
+**Conclusion (reinforces UC-4/UC-5/UC-6):** the `01x16` is NOT the re-enable load and NOT the disable
+timing — it is the DMC GET's **absolute landing phase** relative to `CalculateDMADuration`'s sliding
+`$4000` probe. The disable race only selects WHICH in-flight GET is caught; with RustyNES's APU-rate
+(period/2-1) DMC timer the GET lands inside the measurement window at every offset, while TriCNES's
+continuous CPU-rate period-minus-1 timer lands it outside except at idx 10,11. The genuine fix is the
+single unified CPU-rate continuous DMC byte-timer (UC-1, the master-clock axis), not any `$4015`-side
+lever. The deferred-disable flag is kept default-off as a documented negative result (DO-NOT-RETRY).
